ll who will play. If you succeed in braiding rite and regulation so that a fraction of Blue Hour’s grace stretches across tight weeks, and if you nail the change to bark-ribbons in the Under-Arcum where even smugglers read the walls, then Aurelia will inherit more than a single midnight; it will wake to a practice that does not depend on rumor, only on hands, breath, and time.\",\n      \"objectives\": [\n        \"Conduct a dedication that binds the prism’s new note to a monitored schedule at the Cascadrome.\",\n        \"Assign a public ledger of tuning events carried on bark-ribbons in the Under-Arcum.\",\n        \"Mediate a formal concession from Avar Jen limiting predictive underwriting during Blue Hour.\",\n        \"Announce the founding of a shared school of wind, water, and heat on the Cascadrome’s mid-tier.\"\n      ],\n      \"dialogue\": [\n        {\"speaker\": \"Kael Orisborn\", \"lines\": \"My voice has been quarried smooth by years of ration law, Tallea, but tonight I would rather be a riverbed than a wall. You braided a note that held when history said it should slip, and I respect the stubborn engineering of that mercy. Now the city must learn to lean on this braid without sawing it through with panic, greed, or careless praise. I ask you to speak so the Spire will answer in the only language Aurelia truly obeys: not spectacle that fades, but schedule that endures. If you make this about glory, I will cut your microphone with my own hands, because glory drinks without measuring; if you make it about work, I will carry your tools and sign the logs with my breath. The Stepwell wardens will hold the baseline if you set the tempo in public, and we will show the valves and the minute-marks, not hide them. Remember: austerity is not a virtue when ignorance is the cause; knowledge is our cleanest well, and tonight we open it by timing our vows.\"},\n        {\"speaker\": \"Tallea Miranth\", \"lines\": \"I hear the Heliolith’s thread like a single reed wa